  The RISC Zero zero-knowledge virtual machine (zkVM) is used to prove and verify
  the execution of the ProofReceipt guest programs. The guest compiles to RISC-V
  and is proven with Groth16 using the RISC Zero toolchain (r0vm 3.0.x).
